This paper proposes a method for semantic interpretation of natural language texts using Wikipedia-based concepts. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is typically classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves techniques such as text categorization and computing semantic relatedness, which are related to information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG), respectively. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.LG are also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of common sense and domain-specific knowledge, which are key components of artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the CYC project, which is a well-known effort in the field of knowledge representation and reasoning, falling under cs.CY.
